Dataset

The dataset that we will be using for this analysis is BelkinElagoComplete.

Loading input dataset into our R session for EDA and printing first six rows:

df <- read.csv(file="BelkinElagoComplete.csv", header = TRUE, sep=";")

Variables

The very first thing that youd want to do in your EDA is checking the dimension of the input dataset and the type of variables. In second step we look out for missing values.

basic_eda <- function(data)
plot_missing(df)
plot_histogram(df)

plot_correlation(df, type = 'continuous')

plot_bar(df)

basic_eda(df)
